<section class="hero"><div class="container">
<div class="label">National Index</div>
<h1>Federal Bankruptcy Court Index</h1>
<p>A national, district-level research index covering every US federal bankruptcy court. Each profile presents filing trends, chapter mix, dispositions, prior-filer rate, pro se rate, RECAP coverage, judicial roster, and national rank. Methodology: <a href="/research/methodology/">see how we compute these.</a></p>
</div></section>
<main class="container">
<div class="stat-strip">
<div class="stat-cell"><span class="v">94</span><span class="k">Districts indexed</span></div>
<div class="stat-cell"><span class="v">37,879,715</span><span class="k">Cases in FJC IDB</span></div>
<div class="stat-cell"><span class="v">94</span><span class="k">Federal districts total</span></div>
<div class="stat-cell"><span class="v green">$0</span><span class="k">Cost to access</span></div>
</div>

